==English==


===Etymology===
[[re]] + [[habilitate]]

===Verb===
'''rehabilitate'''
#To [[restore]] or [[repair]], to make [[habitable]] again.
#To [[rescue]] from a state of [[decadence]] or [[decrepitude]].
#To return to [[good grace]]s in the eyes of [[society]] after committing but suffering [[punishment]] for a [[crime]].
The process of restoration of skills by a person who has had an illness or injury so as to regain maximum self-sufficiency and function in a normal or as near normal manner as possible.

===Quotations===
* I turned over the piece of paper, and there, there on the other side, in the middle of the other side, away from everything else on the other side, in parentheses, capital letters, quotated, read the following words:

:: (“KID, HAVE YOU REHABILITATED YOURSELF?”)

: —[[w:Arlo Guthrie|Arlo Guthrie]], [[w:Alice's Restaurant|Alice's Restaurant]], 1967

